(250, 1, '2009-11-22 15:51:07', '2009-11-22 15:51:07', '<strong><span>I don''t know who my grandfather was; I am much more      concerned to know what his grandson will be.</span>\r\n<span>Abraham Lincoln</span></strong>\r\n\r\nIf only the 16th President of the USA had known how important genetic research 	was to become some 150 years afterwards.  As the relentless research into the effects 	of genetics on the human condition continues, even in these early stages, the research 	is providing benefits.  Some human conditions, mainly in the medical field, have been 	attributed to genetic (DNA) makeup.\r\n\r\nFor those of us involved in the genealogy field, either as amateurs or professionals, 	the research is opening up new lines of enquiry especially where the paper trial has 	gone cold. Okay, our real interest is only a small part of this field and is more concerned  	with the X and the Y gene.  The Y gene contributes only some 2% of a man''s genetic make-up 	but the results are quite dramatic!\r\n\r\n<span>dynastyDB</span> is a genealogical tool that aims to marry the standard 	geneological records and yDNA data to form a record of a single surname family over hundreds 	of years.  For more information about dynastyDB, please <a href="/about-dynastydb-the-ydna-database/">click here</a>. 	The application''s developments and other genealogy matters are discussed in the Blog.\r\n\r\nThe application is still in its infancy but already is generating family          trees for public consumption, please see the ''<a href="http://wryellis.mukudu.net/" target="_blank">Ellis Families of West Riding Yorkshire </a>'' website. I hope that feedback both from that          and this site will assist me in improving the application to a point where          I may be able to release the code for other similar studies         of other family names, hopefully to the point that          most popular surnames become available on the Internet.', 'About', 0, '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-dynastyblog', '', '', '2009-11-22 16:30:19', '2009-11-22 16:30:19', '', 0, 'http://www.dynastyblog.net/?page_id=250', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2009-11-22 15:51:03', '2009-11-22 15:51:03', '<strong><span>I don''t know who my grandfather was; I am much more      concerned to know what his grandson will be.</span>\n<span>Abraham Lincoln</span></strong>\n\nIf only the 16th President of the USA had known how important genetic research 	was to become some 150 years afterwards.  As the relentless research into the effects 	of genetics on the human condition continues, even in these early stages, the research 	is providing benefits.  Some human conditions, mainly in the medical field, have been 	attributed to genetic (DNA) makeup.\n\nFor those of us involved in the genealogy field, either as amateurs or professionals, 	the research is opening up new lines of enquiry especially where the paper trial has 	gone cold. Okay, our real interest is only a small part of this field and is more concerned  	with the X and the Y gene.  The Y gene contributes only some 2% of a man''s genetic make-up 	but the results are quite dramatic!\n\n<span>dynastyDB</span> is a genealogical tool that aims to marry the standard 	geneological records and yDNA data to form a record of a single surname family over hundreds 	of years.  For more information about dynastyDB, please <a href="http://www.dynastydb.net/about.html">click here</a>. 	The application''s developments and other genealogy matters are discussed in the Blog.\n\nThe application is still in its infancy but already is generating family          trees for public consumption, please see the ''<a href="http://wryellis.mukudu.net/">Ellis Families of West Riding Yorkshire </a>'' website. I hope that feedback both from that          and this site will assist me in improving the application to a point where          I may be able to release the code for other similar studies         of other family names, hopefully to the point that          most popular surnames become available on the Internet.', 'About DynastyBlog', 0, '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '250-revision',