(259, 1, '2009-11-22 15:57:20', '2009-11-22 15:57:20', 'Standard genealogical data is available from many sources. The major problem with          most of this data is is usually a snapshot of an individual at a certain          point in time. Relationships between events and individuals          is not always obvious from this data except in the case of cencus data.          Over the years, the collection and publication of data has improved and          meets some of the needs of geneologists.\r\n\r\n<!-- Links start -->General Geneology Resources\r\n<blockquote><a href="http://www.genuki.org.uk/" target="genWin">Genuki</a> - the best genelogical resource by far\r\n<a href="http://www.british-genealogy.com/" target="genWin">British Genealogy</a> - Commercial\r\n<a href="http://www.thefamilyhistoryproject.co.uk/" target="genWin">The Family History Project</a></blockquote>\r\nGetting cencus Information\r\n<blockquote>Various Years\r\n<blockquote><a href="http://www.genealogysupplies.com/" target="genWin">Genealogy Supplies</a> - shop online  CD data\r\n<a href="http://www.thegenealogist.co.uk/" target="genWin"> The Genealogist</a> - online name indexes\r\n<a href="http://www.ancestry.co.uk/search/rectype/census/uk/default.aspx" target="genWin">Ancestry.co.uk</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.freecen.org.uk/" target="genWin"> FreeCen</a> - Free but limited</blockquote>\r\n1881\r\n<blockquote><a href="http://www.familysearch.org/Eng/Search/frameset_search.asp?PAGE=census/search_census.asp" target="GenWin">Family Search</a> - another excellent resource</blockquote>\r\n1901\r\n<blockquote><a href="http://www.1901census.nationalarchives.gov.uk/" target="GenWin">1901 Census</a> from the National Archives</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\nBirth, Marriages etc Records\r\n<blockquote>Pre 1837\r\n<blockquote><a href="http://www.familysearch.org/Eng/Search/frameset_search.asp?PAGE=igi/search_IGI.asp&amp;clear_form=true" target="GenWin">Family Search</a> - excellent resource\r\n<a href