(569, 5, '2008-04-02 10:44:38', '2008-04-02 10:44:38', 'We received this news item, too late for inclusion in the May issue of Ancestors Magazine:<br />\n&#34;Professor Robert Bartlett, one of the world''s leading medievalists, is the host on a new landmark history series ''Inside the Medieval Mind''.<br />\n The four-part series, co-produced by The Open University, will explore the mindset and lifestyle of medieval citizens and will reveal what motivated people who lived between 800AD and 1400AD and what beliefs we share with our ancestors. <br />\nThe series, beginning at 9pm on Thursday April 17, is the first in a season of Medieval themed programmes on BBC Four this Spring.&#34;  Find out more at <a href="http://www3.open.ac.uk/media/fullstory.aspx?id=13412">http://www3.open.ac.uk/media/fullstory.aspx?id=13412</a><br />', 'For medievalists everywhere', 0, 'We received this news item, too late for inclusion in the May issue of Ancestors Magazine:<br />\n&#34;Professor Robert Bartlett, one of the world''s leading medievalists, is the host on a new landmark history series ''Inside the Medieval Mind''.<br />\n The four-part series, co-produced by The Open University, will explore the mindset and lifestyle of medieval citizens and will reveal what motivated people who lived between 800AD and 1400AD and what beliefs we share with our ancestors. <br />\nThe series, beginning at 9pm on Thursday April 17, is the first in a season of Medieval themed programmes on BBC Four this Spring.&#34;  Find out more at <a href="http://www3.open.ac.uk/media/fullstory.aspx?id=13412">http://www3.open.ac.uk/media/fullstory.aspx?id=13412</a><br />', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'for-medievalists-everywhere', '', '', '2008-04-02 10:44:38', '2008-04-02 10:44:38', '', 0, 'http://www.ancestorsmagazine.co.uk/?page=blog#78', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2008-04-04 01:00:00', '2008-04-04 00:00:00', 'The Y chromosome retains a remarkable record of human ancestry, passed directly from father to son. In an article in Genome Research, scientists have utilized recently described genetic variations on Y chromosome region that does not undergo recombination to significantly refine the Y chromosome haplogroup tree.', 'Scientists Reshape Y Chromosome Haplogroup Tree Gaining New Insights Into Human Ancestry', 0, 'The Y chromosome retains a remarkable record of human ancestry, passed directly from father to son. In an article in Genome Research, scientists have utilized recently described genetic variations on Y chromosome region that does not undergo recombination to significantly refine the Y chromosome haplogroup tree.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'scientists-reshape-y-chromosome-haplogroup-tree-gaining-new-insights-into-human-ancestry', '', '', '2008-04-04 01:00:00', '2008-04-04 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080401184955.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2008-04-04 13:00:00', '2008-04-04 12:00:00', 'Archaeologists have discovered the oldest known remains of human ancestors in Western Europe. The fossil is about 1.2 million years old. That''s 500,000 years older than the previous oldest known humanlike fossils from the area. The new find bolsters the view that Homo reached Europe not long after leaving Africa almost 2 million years ago.', 'Fossil From Last Common Ancestor Of Neanderthals And Humans Found In Europe, 1.2 Million Years Old', 0, 'Archaeologists have discovered the oldest known remains of human ancestors in Western Europe. The fossil is about 1.2 million years old. That''s 500,000 years older than the previous oldest known humanlike fossils from the area. The new find bolsters the view that Homo reached Europe not long after leaving Africa almost 2 million years ago.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fossil-from-last-common-ancestor-of-neanderthals-and-humans-found-in-europe-12-million-years-old', '', '', '2008-04-04 13:00:00', '2008-04-04 12:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080403185958.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(178, 1, '2008-04-09 07:00:00', '2008-04-09 06:00:00', 'Researchers have developed a technique to detect the ancestry of disease genes in mixed human populations. The technique determines how a set of DNA markers shows the ancestral origin of locations on each chromosome. The team constructed an algorithm for the technique that selects panels of DNA markers that render the best picture of ancestral origin of disease genes.', 'Technique Traces Origins Of Disease Genes In Mixed Human Populations', 0, 'Researchers have developed a technique to detect the ancestry of disease genes in mixed human populations. The technique determines how a set of DNA markers shows the ancestral origin of locations on each chromosome. The team constructed an algorithm for the technique that selects panels of DNA markers that render the best picture of ancestral origin of disease genes.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'technique-traces-origins-of-disease-genes-in-mixed-human-populations', '', '', '2008-04-09 07:00:00', '2008-04-09 06:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080408132122.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2008-04-11 05:00:00', '2008-04-11 04:00:00', 'World War II-era physiologists helped solve physiological problems related to flight, research that helped pave the way for an Allied victory in the air. Physiologists trained a 145-pound St. Bernard dog, Major, to parachute -- simulating the jump of a man. Major wore protective clothing and an oxygen mask and dog paddled during his descent.', 'Historical Look At Physiology And WWII Air War', 0, 'World War II-era physiologists helped solve physiological problems related to flight, research that helped pave the way for an Allied victory in the air. Physiologists trained a 145-pound St. Bernard dog, Major, to parachute -- simulating the jump of a man. Major wore protective clothing and an oxygen mask and dog paddled during his descent.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'historical-look-at-physiology-and-wwii-air-war', '', '', '2008-04-11 05:00:00', '2008-04-11 04:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080411092341.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0),
