(1652, 4, '2010-12-15 13:12:00', '2010-12-15 13:12:00', 'If last year you bought a loved one the camera, this year you could give them the gift of learning how to use it with Blink Photography Courses gift vouchers Ã¢Â€Â“ and save a last minute shopping headache at the same time!<br />\n<br />\nRecently launched by renowned photographers, David Burges and James Fraser, <a href=''http://www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk'' >Blink Photography Courses</a> will give a new lease of life to anyone''s picture taking, from absolute beginners to keen amateurs and even professionals looking to learn some new tricks.<br />\n<br />\nLearning how to use a camera well is a gift that will stay with the recipient through their life. <br />\nWith more and more Britons choosing to hand over cash instead of a wrapped present, the gift vouchers offer a perfect alternative with a more personal touch.<br />\n<br />\nA recent survey showed that more than Ã‚Â£500 million will be handed over this Christmas Day, with more than a third saying they would use it to pay for everyday items such as groceries.<br />\n<br />\nDavid Burges, a winner of the Family Portrait Photographer of the Year award and a sought-after award-winning wedding photographer, said the gift vouchers were ideal for both beginners and advanced photographers.<br />\n<br />\nÃ¢Â€ÂœOur gift vouchers are the perfect choice for anyone who has a camera and wants to learn the secrets of how to capture the perfect shot. And because you can buy them online from <a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk'' href=''http://www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk'' >www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk</a>, it also means you donÃ¢Â€Â™t have to tackle the frantic department stores in the festive rush.<br />\n<br />\nÃ¢Â€ÂœA gift voucher also makes sure the recipient has a brilliant experience, gains knowledge at the same time, and the photographs they learn how to take will last a lifetime Ã¢Â€Â“ which has got to be better than handing over cash for the supermarket shop.Ã¢Â€Â<br />\n<br />\nJames Fraser, famous in photography circles for securing the first, exclusive photographs of Prince William and Prince Harry together, added: Ã¢Â€ÂœMany people are given a camera for Christmas, yet never learn how to get the best out of it, be it a compact or an SLR. Our gift vouchers are available in Ã‚Â£25, Ã‚Â£50 and Ã‚Â£100 amounts and are perfect presents for all keen photographers, right from beginners to semi-professionals and professionals.Ã¢Â€Â <br />\n<br />\nBlink Photography Courses will welcome its first guests at the beginning of March 2011, offering a selection of courses based in Leamington Spa, from classroom-based beginners sessions for compact-weilding novices, to multi-day courses focusing on picturesque parts of the UK and Europe. <br />\n<br />\nENDS<br />\n<br />\nFor more information, please contact: Mark Waugh, Waugh Communications Ltd, at <a title=Sends&nbsp;email&nbsp;to:&nbsp;mark href="mailto:mark@waughcomms.co.uk">mark@waughcomms.co.uk</a> or on 01952 898121.<br />\n<br />\nCaption: Blink Photography Courses gift vouchers.<br />\n<br />\nNOTES TO EDITORS<br />\n<br />\n- Figures taken from a survey from internet bank First Direct, which showed an estimated Ã‚Â£587 million will change hands this Christmas, with nearly two-thirds receiving cash. Four out of 10 people said they would use the money to treat themselves to a luxury item but 36 per cent said they would use it to pay for everyday items such as groceries.<br />\n- Blink Photography Courses will be based primarily in Leamington Spa, with a variety of specialised courses being staged around the UK and picturesque parts of Europe. These will be announced on the website (<a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;http://www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk'' href=''http://www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk'' >http://www.blinkphotographycourses.co.uk</a>).<br />\n- Profiles of David Burges and James Fraser are below Ã¢Â€Â“ and make fascinating reading!<br />\n- Journalists and bloggers are welcome to request places on a course for feature purposes. Please contact Mark Waugh (details above).<br />\n- Blink Photography Courses would be happy to facilitate competitions by supplying vouchers to the value of a day-long course. Again, please contact Mark Waugh to discuss.<br />\n<br />\nAbout David Burges and James Fraser<br />\n<br />\nJames and David have had some of the most distinguished careers of any contemporary UK photographers. Both have spent their working lives covering key momentous events in recent history, as well as getting close to a plethora of A-list of celebrities and politicians, picking up awards along the way.<br />\n<br />\nBiography Ã¢Â€Â“ David Burges<br />\n<br />\nDuring a 16-year career as a staff photographer with the Daily Telegraph, starting at just age 21, David has worked in locations as diverse as the North Pole, Africa, the USA, the Middle East and around Europe. He has covered war in the Balkans, World Cup Finals and the catwalks of New York, Milan, Paris and London, bringing him into contact with supermodels including Kate Moss, Jerry Hall and Marie Helvin.<br />\n<br />\nDavid also covered a number of the adventures of the explorer, David Hempleman Adams, including chasing him in helicopters and planes attempting to photograph him in action as he became the first man to fly an open wicker basket hot air balloon over the Andes, North Pole and across the Atlantic!<br />\n<br />\nAs he wound down his Daily Telegraph career, David launched his own photography business, in the process being named Family Portrait Photographer of the Year in the British Photography Awards. Following this he turned his focus to the top end of the wedding photography market, bringing a photojournlistic style that has won him praise and put him in demand, not to mention securing Photographer of the Year awards from Cosmopolitan Bride and Professional Photographer Magazine.<br />\n<br />\nBiography Ã¢Â€Â“ James Fraser<br />\n<br />\nJames was the man who secured the first, exclusive photographs of Prince William and Prince Harry together as youngsters Ã¢Â€Â“ images which went around the world and were seen in the likes of Time Life, Paris Match, Stern and the News of the World.<br />\n<br />\nBut his working life has encompassed everything the news world has to throw at a photographer, including camping with the Taliban, in Kandahar, from which James recounts discussing the best recipe for lamb curry with a Taliban fighter as US bombers flew overhead...<br />\n<br />\nIt was his time as a royal photographer in the mid-80s that saw him capture that exclusive of the two princes, but in that role he also, inevitably, followed the colourful lives of Princess Diana and Prince Charles Ã¢Â€Â“ not forgetting the Queen, Duke of Edinburgh and the rest of the Royal clan.<br />\n<br />\nAs a news photographer for the Daily Telegraph he has covered every UK General Election since 1992 and his work around politicians has seen him photograph the likes of Bill Clinton, Tony Blair, Vladimir Putin, Margaret Thatcher, John Major, Gordon Brown and David Cameron.<br />\n<br />\nCelebrity photo credits include the ''royalty'' of Hollywood, sports and the international music scene, including George Clooney, Michael Douglas and Catherine Zeta Jones, Tiger Woods, George Clooney, Silvester Stallone, Mick Jagger, Sean Connery... the list goes on.<br />\n<br />\nJames''s newspaper credits are a roll call of the UK''s top titles, either as photographer or picture editor, including The Observer, the Mail on Sunday, the Daily Mail, The Times, The Sunday Times and, of course, The Daily Telegraph.<br />\n<br />\nAs well being a partner in Blink Photography Courses, James is currently a feature and portrait photographer, based in London.<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~4/AZh-U2P_J1w" height="1" width="1"/>