(1564, 4, '2010-08-17 14:39:00', '2010-08-17 14:39:00', 'And what about John Smith and Robin Cook? William HatchettÃ¢Â€Â™s pacey thriller, <a href=''http://www.authonomy.com/books/22558/the-new-labour-papers/read-book/#chapter'' >The New Labour papers</a>, weaves a compelling fiction around the scientistÃ¢Â€Â™s departure and explores other convenient events associated with the rise to power of New Labour.<br />\n<br />\nA decade before David KellyÃ¢Â€Â™s death, on the 11th of May 1994, opposition leader, John Smith, made a fund-raising speech at the Park Lane Hotel for Labour followers. The following morning, he suffered a massive heart attack (the same fate that was to befall Robin Cook, eleven years later). Two months after John SmithÃ¢Â€Â™s death, Tony Blair became party leader. Even if one does not believe in a conspiracy, the event was a transition from dourness, decency and honesty to the slick social climbing, venality and spin doctoring of the Blair and Mandelson era Ã¢Â€Â“ the dynasty of New Labour.<br />\n<br />\nAt the heart of HatchettÃ¢Â€Â™s story, which opens with the death of a scientist clearly based on weapons expert David Kelly, is a fictitious minister, Emma Henderson. She is a sexually-voracious Blairite with a convincing, media-friendly exterior but a dark soul. Henderson slides her way to the top of the greasy pole, using the sadistic door staff of a thinly-disguised south London night club as her fixers and hit men. <br />\n<br />\nWhen the bookÃ¢Â€Â™s hero, Rick Gilliver, a down-at-heel, alcohol-dependent journalist, accidentally discovers her wrong doings, he embarks on a reluctant quest to bring her down.<br />\n<br />\nIn this convincing, close-to-real tale, Henderson is the author or a Ã¢Â€Â˜warped, Machiavellian primerÃ¢Â€Â™, the New Labour papers. This document provides the spine of the story, providing a retrospective gloss on what Hatchett clearly sees as the deceptions and abuses of the New Labour years. <br />\n<br />\nOther leading lights of BlairÃ¢Â€Â™s rise to power are depicted in this roman a clef. For example, future London Mayor Ken Livingstone features, in a dastardly sub-plot in which Henderson tries to have him killed on the Millennium Wheel. <br />\n<br />\nThe book is dripping with a thinly-disguised anger but, in a tradition of political satire that goes back to Dryden and Swift. has enough humour, pace and authorial control to make it a thoroughly enjoyable read.<br />\n<br />\nSeveral recent books have taken a critical look at Tony BlairÃ¢Â€Â™s years at Number Ten. The New Labour papers, which is published on the Harper Collins authonomy website, is the latest and possibly angriest. It could not be more timely or acute, and is ideal to read on a laptop or mobile phone.<br />\n<br />\nRead the book at <a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.authonomy.com'' href=''http://www.authonomy.com'' >www.authonomy.com</a> search The New Labour papers. You can vote for the novel, or encourage your readers to do so, by registering on the website.<br />\n<br />\nJournalist William Hatchett author of <a href=''http://www.authonomy.com/books/22558/the-new-labour-papers/read-book/#chapter'' >The New Labour papers</a>, is available for interview. He can be contacted on 07951 241 822, or emailed at <a title=Sends&nbsp;email&nbsp;to:&nbsp;w.hatchett href="mailto:w.hatchett@virgin.net">w.hatchett@virgin.net</a><br />\n<br />\nYou are welcome to publish extracts of the book provided they are credited to the author, William Hatchett.<br />\n<br />\n - Willliam Hatchett 17-08-2010<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~4/kHdMrBct3sg" height="1" width="1"/>', 'Suspicions around David Kelly''s death', 0, 'And what about John Smith and Robin Cook? William HatchettÃ¢Â€Â™s pacey thriller, The New Labour papers, weaves a compelling fiction around the scientistÃ¢Â€Â™s departure and explores other convenient events associated with the rise to power of New Lab...', 'pending', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-17 14:39:00', '2010-08-17 14:39:00', '', 0, 'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~3/kHdMrBct3sg/rel_display.php', 0, 'post', '', 0),
