(1553, 4, '2010-08-02 09:08:00', '2010-08-02 09:08:00', 'PRESS RELEASE<br />\n<br />\nTHE FUTURE IN THE STARS Ã¢Â€Â“ <br />\nTHE ASTROLOGICAL MESSAGE FOR 2012 AND BEYOND<br />\n<br />\nAugust 2010 - What does the future hold for 2012 and beyond? There has already been much discussion and scepticism about ''2012''.  The Future in the Stars - the astrological message for 2012 and beyond by UK astrologer & broadcaster, Alison Chester-Lambert (Findhorn Press, December 2010, Ã‚Â£9.99) is a no-nonsense analysis of the direction mankind will take in the 21st century, using the predictive science of astrology.  Happily, the book reaches a positive and affirming end that gives REAL trust in our future and a real purpose to our lives.<br />\n<br />\nIn the early years of the 21st century a team of scientists found a whole new family of dwarf planets around Pluto, which was re-categorised to join this group amidst public outcry. They were given the names of little known deities from indigenous peoples - breaking with centuries of tradition of naming planets after Roman gods.  <br />\n<br />\nThe mythology surrounding each of the planets tells us what will become important to the human race in the 21st century because in astrological terms, large fundamental changes in awareness of the Solar System have always coincided with massive fundamental change in the collective consciousness.<br />\n<br />\nSince the astrological aspects for the June solstice of 2012 are more important than the December one, the author discusses the possibility "that the ancient races preceding the Mayans intended to highlight the winter solstice of the Southern hemisphere, that is June 21st 2012, not the winter solstice of the Northern hemisphere.<br />\n<br />\nThe Future in the Stars explains what these discoveries mean for the future of civilisation.  <br />\nAlison Chester-Lambert examines all the latest scientific discoveries in ''astro and particle physics'', comparing ancient spiritual knowledge with current groundbreaking cosmology in a compelling and engaging book.  It is rare to see these two subjects brought together, since neither the scientists nor the spiritually aware have sort to share views with another group they consider un-enlightened. She skilfully weaves the latest scientific discovery with ancient mythology, planetary discovery and spiritual knowledge. <br />\n<br />\nIt opens with Ã¢Â€ÂœTwo thousand years ago three astrologers rode into Jerusalem on camels and announced that a new star in the East meant a messiah would be born.Ã¢Â€Âœ This remains one of the most successful translation jobs done by astrologers and this book aims to follow in that tradition.  <br />\n<br />\nFrom predicting a shift from Christianity to the emergence of Eastern spiritual philosophy,  the re-emergence of the Goddess and the development of sub-atomic power, The Future in the Stars reaches into places that have previously been considered off-limits by social convention, religious prohibition and fear.  The author takes the lid off the Underworld and finds nothing more than a tranquil place of serenity, healing and Kundalini, insisting that there is no such thing as a hidden dimension of evil.  In fact, the idea of burning hell fire and purgatory came from the volcanoes of Italy that surrounded the early Catholic Church.<br />\n<br />\nThe new planets have been named after god/desses from ancient civilisations as far apart as the Arctic, Greece and Polynesia.  One was the god of Easter Island.  He represents fertility, human creation, natural population controls such as pandemics, but he also offers a newly discovered substance that extends life, strategies and a positive resilience.  Once again we will give reverence and respect to Mother Nature and the sacred life force that is present in the Earth and all things.  The religious dynasties of the 20th century gave us the impression that we should worship a single `top` god and not nature. We lost our relationship with the environment and the natural rhythms that are represented by these new god/desses, who will now return. <br />\n   <br />\nThe book also discusses changes in a number of other areas including mother/daughter relationships, rivalry, wealth ethics, flooding and extreme weather events which are represented by a planet that only passes by the Earth every 10,500 years. <br />\n	<br />\nAnd what does this tell us of 2012? The author is able to professionally de-bunk the hype and provide the REAL astrological meaning behind the energy of this special year.  The outrageous claims of apocalypse are simply metaphors from the Collective Unconscious.  It is commonly accepted in psychology that dreams of cataclysm often precede times of great revelation and evolution. We are being raised into wonderful new awareness and Alison sees 2012 as only part of a major shift in the human race which takes place from 2008 until 2016  Alison predicts a knowledge and spiritual Revolution is about to happen. Discover why we are assured of the ultimate protection of the god/desses and the planets that represent them.  After reading The Future in the Stars you will look forward to a positive, less fearful future, knowing where we are going, and why. <br />\n<br />\n-ends-<br />\n<br />\nAll UK publicity enquiries to Sue Blake Media on<br />\n0208 979 5220, 07966 538108, <a title=Sends&nbsp;email&nbsp;to:&nbsp;sue href="mailto:sue@sueblakemedia.co.uk">sue@sueblakemedia.co.uk</a><br />\n<a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.sueblake.com'' href=''http://www.sueblake.com'' >www.sueblake.com</a><br />\n<br />\nThe Future in The Stars, Findhorn Press, December 2010<br />\nISBN: 978 1 84409 505 6<br />\n<br />\nAbout the Author<br />\n<br />\nAlison Chester-Lambert trained at the Faculty of Astrology and then completed a further year at the Centre for Psychological Astrology in Regents College, London. She then worked an astrological telephone consultant for The Sun, The News of the World and the Sunday Times before moving to the Midlands to open the Midlands School of Astrology and a private astrological consultancy practice in 2002. <br />\nAlison writes monthly horoscopes for three regional glossy magazines and is webmaster for two websites. The peer-read professional Astrological Journal regularly publishes her articles. Alison also works for BBC Radio as a consulting astrologer/broadcaster.<br />\n<br />\n<a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.midlandsschoolofastrology.com.uk'' href=''http://www.midlandsschoolofastrology.com.uk'' >www.midlandsschoolofastrology.com.uk</a><br />\n<a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.alisonchesterlambert.com'' href=''http://www.alisonchesterlambert.com'' >www.alisonchesterlambert.com</a><br />\n<br />\n - Sue Blake 02-08-2010<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~4/315xNmB3pK4" height="1" width="1"/>', 'The Future in the Stars - The Astrological Message for 2012 and Beyond', 0, 'PRESS RELEASE\n\nTHE FUTURE IN THE STARS Ã¢Â€Â“ \nTHE ASTROLOGICAL MESSAGE FOR 2012 AND BEYOND\n\nAugust 2010 - What does the future hold for 2012 and beyond? There has already been much discussion and scepticism about ''2012''.  The Future in the Stars - the...', 'pending', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-02 09:08:00', '2010-08-02 09:08:00', '', 0, 'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~3/315xNmB3pK4/rel_display.php', 0, 'post', '', 0),
