(666, 1, '2009-01-03 05:00:00', '2009-01-03 05:00:00', 'The two genes that have the strongest associations with alcohol use and alcohol dependence are mitochondrial aldehyde dehydrogenase 2 and alcohol dehydrogenase IB. Mutations of these genes are considered protective against the risk of developing AD. New research findings show that both Korean ethnicity and ALDH2 genotype may predict drinking behavior among Asian young adults.', 'Ethnicity And The Mitochondrial Aldehyde Dehydrogenase 2 Gene Can Predict Drinking', 0, 'The two genes that have the strongest associations with alcohol use and alcohol dependence are mitochondrial aldehyde dehydrogenase 2 and alcohol dehydrogenase IB. Mutations of these genes are considered protective against the risk of developing AD. New research findings show that both Korean ethnicity and ALDH2 genotype may predict drinking behavior among Asian young adults.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ethnicity-and-the-mitochondrial-aldehyde-dehydrogenase-2-gene-can-predict-drinking', '', '', '2009-01-03 05:00:00', '2009-01-03 05:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/03/090303161305.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0),
