(670, 1, '2009-01-09 05:00:00', '2009-01-09 05:00:00', 'A new study based on DNA analysis from living flowering plants shows that the ancestors of most modern trees diversified extremely rapidly 90 million years ago, ultimately leading to the formation of forests that supported similar evolutionary bursts in animals and other plants.', 'Rapid Burst Of Flowering Plants Set Stage For Other Species', 0, 'A new study based on DNA analysis from living flowering plants shows that the ancestors of most modern trees diversified extremely rapidly 90 million years ago, ultimately leading to the formation of forests that supported similar evolutionary bursts in animals and other plants.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rapid-burst-of-flowering-plants-set-stage-for-other-species', '', '', '2009-01-09 05:00:00', '2009-01-09 05:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/02/090209205204.htm', 0, 'post', '', 0);
