(506, 5, '2009-07-17 11:39:44', '2009-07-17 11:39:44', 'According to Digital Spy website the new series of Who Do You Think You Are? attracted 6.43m (27 percent of the total number of viewers)  making it the most-watched programme between 9pm and 10pm last Wednesday. Its nearest rival, BBC Two''s Dragon''s Den, managed 2.8m viewers.  <br />\nThe opening episode delved into Davina McCall''s family history. To my mind this worked very well with a couple of strong stories, and it was nice to see a star genuinely interested in her ancestry.', 'Who do you think you are?', 0, 'According to Digital Spy website the new series of Who Do You Think You Are? attracted 6.43m (27 percent of the total number of viewers)  making it the most-watched programme between 9pm and 10pm last Wednesday. Its nearest rival, BBC Two''s Dragon''s Den, managed 2.8m viewers.  <br />\nThe opening episode delved into Davina McCall''s family history. To my mind this worked very well with a couple of strong stories, and it was nice to see a star genuinely interested in her ancestry.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'who-do-you-think-you-are', '', '', '2009-07-17 11:39:44', '2009-07-17 11:39:44', '', 0, 'http://www.ancestorsmagazine.co.uk/?page=blog#174', 0, 'post', '', 0),
