(730, 8, '2009-12-29 05:00:00', '2009-12-29 05:00:00', '(<i>American Journal of Pathology</i>) Current research suggests that TNF-receptor associated protein-1 (TRAP-1) may prevent cancer cell death.  The related report by Leav et al., "Cytoprotective Mitochondrial Chaperone TRAP-1 as a Novel Molecular Target in Localized and Metastatic Prostate Cancer," appears in the January 2010 issue of the American Journal of Pathology.', 'The cancer &#039;TRAP&#039;', 0, '(<i>American Journal of Pathology</i>) Current research suggests that TNF-receptor associated protein-1 (TRAP-1) may prevent cancer cell death.  The related report by Leav et al., "Cytoprotective Mitochondrial Chaperone TRAP-1 as a Novel Molecular Target in Localized and Metastatic Prostate Cancer," appears in the January 2010 issue of the American Journal of Pathology.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-cancer-trap', '', '', '2009-12-29 05:00:00', '2009-12-29 05:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2009-12/ajop-tct122909.php', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(731, 17, '2009-12-29 19:45:00', '2009-12-29 19:45:00', 'PITTSBURGH, Dec. 29 /PRNewswire/ -- For the past 30 years, while the rest of the country heads to the mall on the day after Thanksgiving, the Droz Family rises at dawn and hits the road to observe their own annual tradition -- taking a New Years picture in front of a road sign, one with a route number that corresponds to the coming New Year. This year, they''ve compiled the entire collection in a new book, Fellow Travelers, chronicling this three decade project. Originally intended only for friends and family, it''s now available as a free download for anyone who wishes to share their experience without having to get up at 6 AM, complete with postcards, maps, stories and dozens of additional photographs documenting many touching and entertaining moments.', 'New Years Book Chronicles 30-Year Family History', 0, 'PITTSBURGH, Dec. 29 /PRNewswire/ -- For the past 30 years, while the rest of the country heads to the mall on the day after Thanksgiving, the Droz Family rises at dawn and hits the road to observe their own annual tradition -- taking a New Years picture in front of a road sign, one with a route number that corresponds to the coming New Year. This year, they''ve compiled the entire collection in a new book, Fellow Travelers, chronicling this three decade project. Originally intended only for friends and family, it''s now available as a free download for anyone who wishes to share their experience without having to get up at 6 AM, complete with postcards, maps, stories and dozens of additional photographs documenting many touching and entertaining moments.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-years-book-chronicles-30-year-family-history', '', '', '2009-12-29 19:45:00', '2009-12-29 19:45:00', '', 0, 'http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/new-years-book-chronicles-30-year-family-history-80282772.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
