(1351, 1, '2010-06-24 09:54:27', '2010-06-24 09:54:27', 'Want to know more about your genetic roots? Then you are not alone.Â Â  Most tests trace your maternal and paternal lines, by examining genetic markers on the mitochondrial DNA, which is passed from mother to child, or on the Y chromosome, passed from father to son. Like the roots of a tree, however, your genetic roots keep branching the deeper you look: tracing just two of these lines tells you nothing about all the others.\r\n\r\nvia <a href="http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20627651.300-genome-at-10-meet-your-ancestors.html?DCMP=OTC-rss&amp;nsref=online-news">Genome at 10: Meet your ancestors - life - 24 June 2010 - New Scientist</a>.', 'Meet Your Ancestors - Genetic Testing', 0, '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'meet-your-ancestors-genetic-testing', '', '', '2010-06-24 09:54:27', '2010-06-24 09:54:27', '', 0, 'http://www.dynastyblog.net/?p=1351', 0, 'post', '', 0),
