(1609, 4, '2010-10-06 09:00:00', '2010-10-06 09:00:00', 'LifeÃ¢Â€Â™s a journey, Save Every Step<br />\nNew website brings old memories to life<br />\n<br />\nHappy memories of summer fun donÃ¢Â€Â™t have to fade along with your tan, thanks to a new life story website. <br />\nEveryone has them, those precious little memories that weave the texture of life, in between the big events, like the first day at school or last day at work. Teddy bears and boyfriends, haircuts and wedding dresses, the birth of a baby or the patter of her first steps. Capturing all these memories, big and small, and making sure they never get forgotten, was the inspiration for SaveEveryStep.com.<br />\n<br />\nA life story  is laid out on a Ã¢Â€Â˜LifelineÃ¢Â€Â™, the scrollable, zoomable heart of the site, where all the episodes that make your unique life are set out as a journey through the days and years. A choice of security settings gives you control over who sees the various elements in your story.<br />\n<br />\nÃ¢Â€ÂœI lost my mum suddenly whilst I was pregnant with my son. They never met. I wanted to Ã¢Â€Â˜saveÃ¢Â€Â™ her and embed her into our family history for future generations to come. The boxes of sepia photos get damaged and dispersed, but SaveEveryStep  is a visually exciting, permanent record of the 71 years of her life; her joys and her tragedies and what shaped her as a person.Ã¢Â€Â Ã¢Â€Â“ Helen Spencer, the founder of the site.<br />\n<br />\nSaveEveryStep lets you build life stories from those fleeting moments online, and share them instantly with friends and family on an interactive timeline. A sort of digital diary which lays out the precious events of your life in the order they happened Ã¢Â€Â“ step by step. Photos and other media enrich the expandable events, and everything can be kept safely in an online vault, where theyÃ¢Â€Â™ll never get faded, damaged or lost.<br />\n<br />\n Ã¢Â€ÂœMy kids regularly bring home masterful works of art from school,Ã¢Â€Â said Helen. Ã¢Â€ÂœBut they spend a week on the fridge door and then get lost or chewed up. Capturing the continuous story of a childÃ¢Â€Â™s development from birth to adulthood is a treasure which I, and they, can look back on in years to come. Being able to watch the kids grow up all over again, or even raid the family album for pictures of my own childhood was part of the inspiration for SaveEveryStep.Ã¢Â€Â<br />\n<br />\n<a title=''Goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;website&nbsp;of:&nbsp;www.SaveEveryStep.com'' href=''http://www.saveeverystep.com'' >www.SaveEveryStep.com</a> is completely FREE to register and use, and even the family pets can have their own Lifelines!<br />\nFor more information, contact Helen Spencer at <a title=Sends&nbsp;email&nbsp;to:&nbsp;helen.spencer href="mailto:helen.spencer@saveeverystep.com">helen.spencer@saveeverystep.com</a>, or on 07957627217.<br />\n<a href=''http://saveeverystep.com'' >life''sajourney</a><br />\n<br />\n - Helen Spencer 06-10-2010<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~4/AfRgIlcj3No" height="1" width="1"/>', 'Life''s a journey....SaveEveryStep', 0, 'LifeÃ¢Â€Â™s a journey, Save Every Step\nNew website brings old memories to life\n\nHappy memories of summer fun donÃ¢Â€Â™t have to fade along with your tan, thanks to a new life story website. \nEveryone has them, those precious little memories that weave ...', 'pending', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-06 09:00:00', '2010-10-06 09:00:00', '', 0, 'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ReleaseWireLeisureAndHobbies/~3/AfRgIlcj3No/rel_display.php', 0, 'post', '', 0),
